==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*arsaz'', from Indo-European ''*ors-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[ers]], Old Saxon [[ars]] (Dutch [[aars]]), Old High German [[ars]] (German [[Arsch]]), Old Norse [[ars]] (Danish [[ars]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Hittite ''ārraš'', Old Irish [[err]], Greek [[όρρος]].

